0152chik.dexEntry: In battle, Chikorita waves its leaf around to keep the foe at bay. However, a sweet fragrance also wafts from the leaf, becalming the battling Pokémon and creating a cozy, friendly atmosphere all around.

0153bayl.dexEntry: Bayleef's neck is ringed by curled-up leaves. Inside each tubular leaf is a small shoot of a tree. The fragrance of this shoot makes people peppy.

0154mega.dexEntry: The fragrance of Meganium's flower soothes and calms emotions. In battle, this Pokémon gives off more of its becalming scent to blunt the foe's fighting spirit.

0155cynd.dexEntry: Cyndaquil protects itself by flaring up the flames on its back. The flames are vigorous if the Pokémon is angry. However, if it is tired, the flames splutter fitfully with incomplete combustion.

0156quil.dexEntry: Quilava keeps its foes at bay with the intensity of its flames and gusts of superheated air. This Pokémon applies its outstanding nimbleness to dodge attacks even while scorching the foe with flames.

0158toto.dexEntry: Despite the smallness of its body, Totodile's jaws are very powerful. While the Pokémon may think it is just playfully nipping, its bite has enough power to cause serious injury.

0159croc.dexEntry: Once Croconaw has clamped its jaws on its foe, it will absolutely not let go. Because the tips of its fangs are forked back like barbed fishhooks, they become impossible to remove when they have sunk in.

0160fera.dexEntry: Feraligatr intimidates its foes by opening its huge mouth. In battle, it will kick the ground hard with its thick and powerful hind legs to charge at the foe at an incredible speed.

0161sent.dexEntry: When Sentret sleeps, it does so while another stands guard. The sentry wakes the others at the first sign of danger. When this Pokémon becomes separated from its pack, it becomes incapable of sleep due to fear.

0162furr.dexEntry: Furret has a very slim build. When under attack, it can slickly squirm through narrow spaces and get away. In spite of its short limbs, this Pokémon is very nimble and fleet.

0163hoot.dexEntry: Hoothoot has an internal organ that senses and tracks the earth's rotation. Using this special organ, this Pokémon begins hooting at precisely the same time every day.

0164noct.dexEntry: Noctowl never fails at catching prey in darkness. This Pokémon owes its success to its superior vision that allows it to see in minimal light, and to its soft, supple wings that make no sound in flight.

0165ledy.dexEntry: They are timid and grow uneasy when not in a swarm with others of their kind. The pattern on their backs differs slightly from one to another.

0166ledi.dexEntry: While it's believed that starlight provides it with energy, this Pokémon also loves to eat berries. In the daytime, it curls up in the grass to sleep.

0167spin.dexEntry: Some fishermen weave its sturdy thread into nets to catch fish Pokémon.

0168aria.dexEntry: It spins thread from both its rear and its mouth. Then it wraps its prey up in thread and sips their bodily fluids at its leisure.

0169crob.dexEntry: Both its legs became wings, and as a result, it can't move well on the ground. All it can do is crawl around.

0170chin.dexEntry: It lives in the depths beyond the reach of sunlight. It flashes lights on its antennae to communicate with others of its kind.

0171lant.dexEntry: This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.

0172pich.dexEntry: It is not yet skilled at controlling electricity. If you take your eyes off it, it may shock itself.

0173clef.dexEntry: Because of its silhouette, it's believed to be a star reborn. For some reason, it loves <<0774mini>>.

0174iggl.dexEntry: It likes to sing but is not yet good at it. With praise and encouragement, it will get better little by little.

0175toge.dexEntry: As its energy, Togepi uses the positive emotions of compassion and pleasure exuded by people and Pokémon. This Pokémon stores up feelings of happiness inside its shell, then shares them with others.

0176toge.dexEntry: Togetic is said to be a Pokémon that brings good fortune. When the Pokémon spots someone who is pure of heart, it is said to appear and share its happiness with that person.

0177natu.dexEntry: Natu cannot fly because its wings are not yet fully grown. If your eyes meet with this Pokémon's eyes, it will stare back intently at you. But if you move even slightly, it will hop away to safety.It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.

0178xatu.dexEntry: Xatu stands rooted and still in one spot all day long. People believe that this Pokémon does so out of fear of the terrible things it has foreseen in the future.

0179mare.dexEntry: Mareep's fluffy coat of wool rubs together and builds a static charge. The more static electricity is charged, the more brightly the lightbulb at the tip of its tail glows.

0180flaa.dexEntry: Flaaffy's wool quality changes so that it can generate a high amount of static electricity with a small amount of wool. The bare and slick parts of its hide are shielded against electricity.

0181amph.dexEntry: Ampharos gives off so much light that it can be seen even from space. People in the old days used the light of this Pokémon to send signals back and forth with others far away.

0182bell.dexEntry: A Bellossom grows flowers more beautifully if it has evolved from a smelly <<0044gloo>>—the more stinky the better. At night, this Pokémon closes its petals and goes to sleep.

0183mari.dexEntry: When fishing for food at the edge of a fast-running stream, Marill wraps its tail around the trunk of a tree. This Pokémon's tail is flexible and configured to stretch.

0184azum.dexEntry: Azumarill can make balloons out of air. It makes these air balloons if it spots a drowning Pokémon. The air balloons enable the Pokémon in trouble to breathe.

0185sudo.dexEntry: To avoid attack, it mimics a tree. It will run off if splashed with water, which it hates.

0186poli.dexEntry: It's the leader of <<0060poli>> and <<0061poli>>. When Politoed roars, they all cower in fear.

0187hopp.dexEntry: This Pokémon drifts and floats with the wind. If it senses the approach of strong winds, Hoppip links its leaves with other Hoppip to prepare against being blown away.

0188skip.dexEntry: Skiploom's flower blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees Fahrenheit. How much the flower opens depends on the temperature. For that reason, this Pokémon is sometimes used as a thermometer.

0189jump.dexEntry: Jumpluff rides warm southern winds to cross the sea and fly to foreign lands. The Pokémon descends to the ground when it encounters cold air while it is floating.

0190aipo.dexEntry: Aipom's tail ends in a hand-like appendage that can be cleverly manipulated. However, because the Pokémon uses its tail so much, its real hands have become rather clumsy.

0191sunk.dexEntry: Sunkern tries to move as little as it possibly can. It does so because it tries to conserve all the nutrients it has stored in its body for its evolution. It will not eat a thing, subsisting only on morning dew.

0192sunf.dexEntry: Sunflora converts solar energy into nutrition. It moves around actively in the daytime when it is warm. It stops moving as soon as the sun goes down for the night.

0193yanm.dexEntry: Yanma is capable of seeing 360 degrees without having to move its eyes. It is a great flier that is adept at making sudden stops and turning midair. This Pokémon uses its flying ability to quickly chase down targeted prey.

0194woop.dexEntry: Wooper usually lives in water. However, it occasionally comes out onto land in search of food. On land, it coats its body with a gooey, toxic film.

0195quag.dexEntry: Quagsire hunts for food by leaving its mouth wide open in water and waiting for its prey to blunder in unaware. Because the Pokémon does not move, it does not get very hungry.

0196espe.dexEntry: It can instantaneously sense its opponent's movements by feeling air currents with its fine fur.

0197umbr.dexEntry: With its black fur, it blends into the darkness. It bides its time, and when prey appears, this Pokémon goes for its throat, and then eats it.

0198murk.dexEntry: They awaken at dusk and take wing in the twilight, leading to the expression, "Get home before the Murkrow fly".

0200misd.dexEntry: It will use any means necessary to frighten people and absorb their life energy. It practices constantly to hone its skill in causing fear.

0201unow.dexEntry: This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.

0202wobb.dexEntry: Wobbuffet does nothing but endure attacks—it won't attack on its own. However, it won't endure an attack on its tail. When that happens, the Pokémon will try to take the foe with it using Destiny Bond.

0203gira.dexEntry: Girafarig's rear head also has a brain, but it is small. The rear head attacks in response to smells and sounds. Approaching this Pokémon from behind can cause the rear head to suddenly lash out and bite.

0204pine.dexEntry: Pineco hangs from a tree branch and patiently waits for prey to come along. If the Pokémon is disturbed while eating by someone shaking its tree, it drops down to the ground and explodes with no warning.

0205forr.dexEntry: Forretress conceals itself inside its hardened steel shell. The shell is opened when the Pokémon is catching prey, but it does so at such a quick pace that the shell's inside cannot be seen.

0206duns.dexEntry: Dunsparce has a drill for its tail. It uses this tail to burrow into the ground backward. This Pokémon is known to make its nest in complex shapes deep under the ground.

0207glig.dexEntry: Gligar glides through the air without a sound as if it were sliding. This Pokémon hangs on to the face of its foe using its clawed hind legs and the large pincers on its forelegs, then injects the prey with its poison barb.

0208stee.dexEntry: Steelix lives even further underground than <<0095onix>>. This Pokémon is known to dig toward the earth's core. There are records of this Pokémon reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.

0209snub.dexEntry: Despite its intimidating face, it's quite cowardly. Its desperate attempts to appear threatening make it popular with people.

0210gran.dexEntry: Its well-developed lower jaw and heavy fangs are its weapons. As long as it's not provoked, it rarely bites.

0212sciz.dexEntry: It uses its wings to adjust its body temperature. Otherwise, its metal body would become too hot and melt in the heat of battle.

0213shuc.dexEntry: Shuckle quietly hides itself under rocks, keeping its body concealed inside its hard shell while eating berries it has stored away. The berries mix with its body fluids to become a juice.

0214hera.dexEntry: Heracross has sharp claws on its feet. These are planted firmly into the ground or the bark of a tree, giving the Pokémon a secure and solid footing to forcefully fling away foes with its proud horn.

0216tedd.dexEntry: This Pokémon likes to lick its palms that are sweetened by being soaked in honey. Teddiursa concocts its own honey by blending fruits and pollen collected by <<0015beed>>.

0217ursa.dexEntry: In the forests inhabited by Ursaring, it is said that there are many streams and towering trees where they gather food. This Pokémon walks through its forest gathering food every day.

0218slug.dexEntry: Molten magma courses throughout Slugma's circulatory system. If this Pokémon is chilled, the magma cools and hardens. Its body turns brittle and chunks fall off, reducing its size.

0219magc.dexEntry: Magcargo's shell is actually its skin that hardened as a result of cooling. Its shell is very brittle and fragile—just touching it causes it to crumble apart. This Pokémon returns to its original size by dipping itself in magma.

0220swin.dexEntry: Swinub roots for food by rubbing its snout against the ground. Its favorite food is a mushroom that grows under the cover of dead grass. This Pokémon occasionally roots out hot springs.

0221pilo.dexEntry: Piloswine is covered by a thick coat of long hair that enables it to endure the freezing cold. This Pokémon uses its tusks to dig up food that has been buried under ice.

0223remo.dexEntry: Remoraid sucks in water, then expels it at high velocity using its abdominal muscles to shoot down flying prey. When evolution draws near, this Pokémon travels downstream from rivers.

0224octi.dexEntry: Octillery grabs onto its foe using its tentacles. This Pokémon tries to immobilize it before delivering the finishing blow. If the foe turns out to be too strong, Octillery spews ink to escape.

0225deli.dexEntry: Although it naturally prefers colder locales, Delibird in Alola seem able to withstand the heat to a certain extent.

0226mant.dexEntry: On sunny days, schools of Mantine can be seen elegantly leaping over the sea's waves. This Pokémon is not bothered by the <<0223remo>> that hitches rides.

0227skar.dexEntry: Its metal body is sturdy, but it does rust rather easily. So on rainy days, this Pokémon prefers to stay put in its nest.

0228houn.dexEntry: Houndour hunt as a coordinated pack. They communicate with each other using a variety of cries to corner their prey. This Pokémon's remarkable teamwork is unparalleled.

0229houn.dexEntry: In a Houndoom pack, the one with its horns raked sharply toward the back serves a leadership role. These Pokémon choose their leader by fighting among themselves.

0230king.dexEntry: Kingdra sleeps on the seafloor where it is otherwise devoid of life. When a storm arrives, the Pokémon is said to awaken and wander about in search of prey.

0231phan.dexEntry: For its nest, Phanpy digs a vertical pit in the ground at the edge of a river. It marks the area around its nest with its trunk to let the others know that the area has been claimed.

0232donp.dexEntry: Donphan's favorite attack is curling its body into a ball, then charging at its foe while rolling at high speed. Once it starts rolling, this Pokémon can't stop very easily.

0233pory.dexEntry: <<0137pory>> was updated to a new version in readiness for planetary development. But that dream remains unrealized as yet.

0234stan.dexEntry: Stantler's magnificent antlers were traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this Pokémon was hunted close to extinction by those who were after the priceless antlers.

0235smea.dexEntry: The unique creations produced by each Smeargle are painted using the fluid that oozes from its tail. This is how it marks its territory.

0236tyro.dexEntry: Tyrogue becomes stressed out if it does not get to train every day. When raising this Pokémon, the Trainer must establish and uphold various training methods.

0237hitm.dexEntry: Hitmontop spins on its head at high speed, all the while delivering kicks. This technique is a remarkable mix of both offense and defense at the same time. The Pokémon travels faster spinning than it does walking.

0238smoo.dexEntry: Smoochum actively runs about, but also falls quite often. Whenever the chance arrives, it will look for its reflection to make sure its face hasn't become dirty.

0239elek.dexEntry: When it's in a house, electrical outlets serve as its baby bottles. It sucks down electricity.

0240magb.dexEntry: A famous potter lives with a Magby. Apparently its soft flames produce fine works.

0241milt.dexEntry: Its milk is high in calories and packed with nutrients. Therefore, if you drink too much of it, you may wind up with a body like Miltank's.

0242blis.dexEntry: Its fluffy fur coat acts as a sensor, enabling it to read the feelings of people and Pokémon.

0243raik.dexEntry: Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

0244ente.dexEntry: Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.

0245suic.dexEntry: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

0246larv.dexEntry: Larvitar is born deep under the ground. To come up to the surface, this Pokémon must eat its way through the soil above. Until it does so, Larvitar cannot see its parents.

0247pupi.dexEntry: Pupitar creates a gas inside its body that it compresses and forcefully ejects to propel itself like a jet. The body is very durable—it avoids damage even if it hits solid steel.

0248tyra.dexEntry: Tyranitar is so overwhelmingly powerful, it can bring down a whole mountain to make its nest. This Pokémon wanders about in mountains seeking new opponents to fight.

0249lugi.dexEntry: Lugia's wings pack devastating power—a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this Pokémon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.

0250hooh.dexEntry: Ho-Oh's feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

0251cele.dexEntry: This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.

0252tree.dexEntry: Treecko has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This Pokémon attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.

0253grov.dexEntry: The leaves growing out of Grovyle's body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This Pokémon is a master at climbing trees in jungles.

0254scep.dexEntry: The leaves growing on Sceptile's body are very sharp edged. This Pokémon is very agile—it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

0255torc.dexEntry: Torchic has a place inside its body where it keeps its flame. Give it a hug—it will be glowing with warmth. This Pokémon is covered all over by a fluffy coat of down.

0256comb.dexEntry: Combusken battles with the intensely hot flames it spews from its beak and with outstandingly destructive kicks. This Pokémon's cry is very loud and distracting.

0257blaz.dexEntry: Blaziken has incredibly strong legs—it can easily clear a 30-story building in one leap. This Pokémon's blazing punches leave its foes scorched and blackened.

0258mudk.dexEntry: The fin on Mudkip's head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this Pokémon can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.

0259mars.dexEntry: The surface of Marshtomp's body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This Pokémon plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.

0260swam.dexEntry: Swampert is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This Pokémon also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.

0261pooc.dexEntry: At first sight, Poochyena takes a bite at anything that moves. This Pokémon chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it may turn tail if the prey strikes back.

0262migh.dexEntry: Mightyena gives obvious signals when it is preparing to attack. It starts to growl deeply and then flattens its body. This Pokémon will bite savagely with its sharply pointed fangs.

0265wurm.dexEntry: Using the spikes on its rear end, Wurmple peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This Pokémon's feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.

0266silc.dexEntry: Silcoon tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There, this Pokémon hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.

0267beau.dexEntry: Beautifly's favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this Pokémon, just leave a potted flower by an open window. Beautifly is sure to come looking for pollen.

0268casc.dexEntry: If it is attacked, Cascoon remains motionless however badly it may be hurt. It does so because if it were to move, its body would be weak upon evolution. This Pokémon will also not forget the pain it endured.

0269dust.dexEntry: When Dustox flaps its wings, a fine dust is scattered all over. This dust is actually a powerful poison that will even make a pro wrestler sick. This Pokémon searches for food using its antennae like radar.

0270lota.dexEntry: Lotad live in ponds and lakes, where they float on the surface. It grows weak if its broad leaf dies. On rare occasions, this Pokémon travels on land in search of clean water.

0271lomb.dexEntry: Lombre is nocturnal—it will get active after dusk. It is also a mischief maker. When this Pokémon spots anglers, it tugs on their fishing lines from beneath the surface and enjoys their consternation.

0272ludi.dexEntry: Ludicolo begins dancing as soon as it hears cheerful, festive music. This Pokémon is said to appear when it hears the singing of children on hiking outings.

0273seed.dexEntry: Seedot looks exactly like an acorn when it is dangling from a tree branch. It startles other Pokémon by suddenly moving. This Pokémon polishes its body once a day using leaves.

0274nuzl.dexEntry: This Pokémon pulls out the leaf on its head and makes a flute with it. The sound of Nuzleaf's flute strikes fear and uncertainty in the hearts of people lost in a forest.

0275shif.dexEntry: Shiftry's large fans generate awesome gusts of wind at a speed close to 100 feet per second. The whipped-up wind blows anything away. This Pokémon chooses to live quietly deep in forests.

0276tail.dexEntry: Taillow courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy Pokémon will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.

0277swel.dexEntry: Swellow flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This Pokémon dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by Swellow's clawed feet, preventing escape.

0278wing.dexEntry: Fishermen keep an eye out for Wingull in the sky, because wherever they're circling, the ocean is sure to be teeming with fish Pokémon.

0279peli.dexEntry: Gathering food is the work of young males. They store food in their capacious beaks and carry it back to others waiting in the nest.

0280ralt.dexEntry: Ralts senses the emotions of people using the horns on its head. This Pokémon rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws closer if it senses that the person has a positive disposition.

0281kirl.dexEntry: It is said that a Kirlia that is exposed to the positive emotions of its Trainer grows beautiful. This Pokémon controls psychokinetic powers with its highly developed brain.

0282gard.dexEntry: Gardevoir has the ability to read the future. If it senses impending danger to its Trainer, this Pokémon is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at full power.

0283surs.dexEntry: It moves as if skating on the surface of the water. It often fights with <<0751dewp>> over food.

0284masq.dexEntry: It intimidates enemies with the eye-like patterns on its antennae. Its four wings allow it to fly in any direction.

0285shro.dexEntry: Shroomish live in damp soil in the dark depths of forests. They are often found keeping still under fallen leaves. This Pokémon feeds on compost that is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.

0286brel.dexEntry: Breloom closes in on its foe with light and sprightly footwork, then throws punches with its stretchy arms. This Pokémon's fighting technique puts boxers to shame.

0287slak.dexEntry: Slakoth's heart beats just once a minute. Whatever happens, it is content to loaf around motionless. It is rare to see this Pokémon in motion.

0288vigo.dexEntry: Vigoroth is simply incapable of remaining still. Even when it tries to sleep, the blood in its veins grows agitated, compelling this Pokémon to run wild throughout the jungle before it can settle down.

0289slak.dexEntry: Wherever Slaking live, rings of over a yard in diameter appear in grassy fields. They are made by the Pokémon as it eats all the grass within reach while lying prone on the ground.

0290ninc.dexEntry: Nincada lives underground for many years in complete darkness. This Pokémon absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees. It stays motionless as it waits for evolution.

0291ninj.dexEntry: Ninjask moves around at such a high speed that it cannot be seen, even while its crying can be clearly heard. For that reason, this Pokémon was long believed to be invisible.

0292shed.dexEntry: Shedinja's hard body doesn't move—not even a twitch. In fact, its body appears to be merely a hollow shell. It is believed that this Pokémon will steal the spirit of anyone peering into its hollow body from its back.

0293whis.dexEntry: Whismur is very timid. If it starts to cry loudly, it becomes startled by its own crying and cries even harder. When it finally stops crying, the Pokémon goes to sleep, all tired out.

0294loud.dexEntry: Loudred shouts while stamping its feet. After it finishes shouting, this Pokémon becomes incapable of hearing anything for a while. This is considered to be a weak point.

0295expl.dexEntry: Exploud communicates its feelings to the others by emitting whistle-like sounds from the tubes on its body. This Pokémon only raises its voice when it is in battle.

0296maku.dexEntry: It was originally brought in from another region, but now Makuhita from Alola are more famous.

0297hari.dexEntry: It is known for its fantastic strength, but as it grows older, it focuses more on training <<0296maku>>.

0298azur.dexEntry: Azurill's tail is large and bouncy. It is packed full of the nutrients this Pokémon needs to grow. Azurill can be seen bouncing and playing on its big, rubbery tail.

0299nose.dexEntry: The magnet in Nosepass's nose provides an unerring compass, making it an excellent partner for Trainers going on a journey.

0300skit.dexEntry: Skitty has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This Pokémon is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.

0301delc.dexEntry: Delcatty prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this Pokémon eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.

0302sabl.dexEntry: This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it's believed that Sableye will steal people's spirits away.

0303mawi.dexEntry: Mawile's huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed. Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard. When the foe least expects it, Mawile chomps it with its gaping jaws.

0304aron.dexEntry: Aron has a body of steel. With one all-out charge, this Pokémon can demolish even a heavy dump truck. The destroyed dump truck then becomes a handy meal for the Pokémon.

0305lair.dexEntry: Lairon feeds on iron contained in rocks and water. It makes its nest on mountains where iron ore is buried. As a result, the Pokémon often clashes with humans mining the iron ore.

0306aggr.dexEntry: Aggron is protective of its environment. If its mountain is ravaged by a landslide or a fire, this Pokémon will haul topsoil to the area, plant trees, and beautifully restore its own territory.

0307medi.dexEntry: Meditite undertakes rigorous mental training deep in the mountains. However, whenever it meditates, this Pokémon always loses its concentration and focus. As a result, its training never ends.

0308medi.dexEntry: It is said that through meditation, Medicham heightens energy inside its body and sharpens its sixth sense. This Pokémon hides its presence by merging itself with fields and mountains.

0309elec.dexEntry: Electrike stores electricity in its long body hair. This Pokémon stimulates its leg muscles with electric charges. These jolts of power give its legs explosive acceleration performance.

0310mane.dexEntry: Manectric is constantly discharging electricity from its mane. The sparks sometimes ignite forest fires. When it enters a battle, this Pokémon creates thunderclouds.

0311plus.dexEntry: When Plusle is cheering on its partner, it flashes with electric sparks from all over its body. If its partner loses, this Pokémon cries loudly.

0312minu.dexEntry: Minun is more concerned about cheering on its partners than its own safety. It shorts out the electricity in its body to create brilliant showers of sparks to cheer on its teammates.

0313volb.dexEntry: Volbeat's tail glows like a lightbulb. With other Volbeat, it uses its tail to draw geometric shapes in the night sky. This Pokémon loves the sweet aroma given off by <<0314illu>>.

0314illu.dexEntry: Illumise attracts a swarm of <<0313volb>> using a sweet fragrance. Once the <<0313volb>> have gathered, this Pokémon leads the lit-up swarm in drawing geometric designs on the canvas of the night sky.

0315rose.dexEntry: On extremely rare occasions, a Roselia is said to appear with its flowers in unusual colors. The thorns on this Pokémon's head contain a vicious poison.

0316gulp.dexEntry: Virtually all of Gulpin's body is its stomach. As a result, it can swallow something its own size. This Pokémon's stomach contains a special fluid that digests anything.

0317swal.dexEntry: Swalot has no teeth, so what it eats, it swallows whole, no matter what. Its cavernous mouth yawns widely. An automobile tire could easily fit inside this Pokémon's mouth.

0318carv.dexEntry: Each school has its own territory. Any intruders are mercilessly attacked with fangs bared.

0319shar.dexEntry: It pursues its prey at speeds of 75 mph and finishes them off with fangs that can crush iron. It is known as the bully of the sea.

0320wail.dexEntry: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of <<0746wish>> every day.

0321wail.dexEntry: Its immense size is the reason for its popularity. Wailord watching is a favorite sightseeing activity in various parts of the world.

0322nume.dexEntry: Numel is extremely dull witted—it doesn't notice being hit. However, it can't stand hunger for even a second. This Pokémon's body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.

0323came.dexEntry: Camerupt has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this Pokémon's back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.

0324tork.dexEntry: If the fire burning within its shell goes out, it will die. Those who wish to raise one in their home must always keep something flammable at hand.

0325spoi.dexEntry: Spoink keeps a pearl on top of its head. The pearl functions to amplify this Pokémon's psychokinetic powers. It is therefore on a constant search for a bigger pearl.

0326grum.dexEntry: Grumpig uses the black pearls on its body to wield its fantastic powers. When it is doing so, it dances bizarrely. This Pokémon's black pearls are valuable as works of art.

0327spin.dexEntry: Its steps are staggering and unsteady, but Spinda thinks it's walking in a straight line.

0328trap.dexEntry: As it digs through the sand, its giant jaws crush any rocks that obstruct its path. It builds a funnel-shaped nest.

0329vibr.dexEntry: To help make its wings grow, it dissolves quantities of prey in its digestive juices and guzzles them down every day.

0330flyg.dexEntry: This Pokémon hides in the heart of sandstorms it creates and seldom appears where people can see it.

0331cacn.dexEntry: Cacnea lives in arid locations such as deserts. It releases a strong aroma from its flower to attract prey. When prey comes near, this Pokémon shoots sharp thorns from its body to bring the victim down.

0332cact.dexEntry: During the daytime, Cacturne remains unmoving so that it does not lose any moisture to the harsh desert sun. This Pokémon becomes active at night when the temperature drops.

0333swab.dexEntry: Swablu loves to make things clean. If it spots something dirty, it will wipe and polish it with its cottony wings. If its wings become dirty, this Pokémon finds a stream and showers itself.

0334alta.dexEntry: Altaria sings in a gorgeous soprano. Its wings are like cotton clouds. This Pokémon catches updrafts with its buoyant wings and soars way up into the wild blue yonder.

0335zang.dexEntry: Memories of battling its archrival <<0336sevi>> are etched into every cell of Zangoose's body. This Pokémon adroitly dodges attacks with incredible agility.

0336sevi.dexEntry: Seviper's swordlike tail serves two purposes—it slashes foes and douses them with secreted poison. This Pokémon will not give up its long-running blood feud with <<0335zang>>.

0337luna.dexEntry: Lunatone was discovered at a location where a meteoroid fell. As a result, some people theorize that this Pokémon came from space. However, no one has been able to prove this theory so far.

0338solr.dexEntry: Sunlight is the source of Solrock's power. It is said to possess the ability to read the emotions of others. This Pokémon gives off intense heat while rotating its body.

0339barb.dexEntry: Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in muddy waters, it can detect its prey's location.

0340whis.dexEntry: A glutton that devours anything that moves, it quietly lurks at the bottom of swamps, lying in wait for prey.

0341corp.dexEntry: Corphish catches prey with its sharp claws. It has no likes or dislikes when it comes to food—it will eat anything. This Pokémon has no trouble living in filthy water.

0342craw.dexEntry: Crawdaunt molts (sheds) its shell regularly. Immediately after molting, its shell is soft and tender. Until the shell hardens, this Pokémon hides in its streambed burrow to avoid attack from its foes.

0343balt.dexEntry: Baltoy moves while spinning around on its one foot. Primitive wall paintings depicting this Pokémon living among people were discovered in some ancient ruins.

0344clay.dexEntry: Claydol are said to be dolls of mud made by primitive humans and brought to life by exposure to a mysterious ray. This Pokémon moves about while levitating.

0345lile.dexEntry: Lileep is an ancient Pokémon that was regenerated from a fossil. It remains permanently anchored to a rock. From its immobile perch, this Pokémon intently scans for prey with its two eyes.

0346crad.dexEntry: Cradily's body serves as an anchor, preventing it from being washed away in rough seas. This Pokémon secretes a strong digestive fluid from its tentacles.

0347anor.dexEntry: Anorith was regenerated from a prehistoric fossil. This primitive Pokémon once lived in warm seas. It grips its prey firmly between its two large claws.

0348arma.dexEntry: Armaldo's tough armor makes all attacks bounce off. This Pokémon's two enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. They have the power to punch right through a steel slab.

0349feeb.dexEntry: Although unattractive and unpopular, this Pokémon's marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.

0350milo.dexEntry: It lives at the bottom of clear lakes. In times of war, it shows itself, which soothes people's minds and hearts.

0351cast.dexEntry: It changes its form depending on the weather. Changes in the temperature or humidity appear to affect its cellular structure.

0352kecl.dexEntry: Kecleon is capable of changing its body colors at will to blend in with its surroundings. There is one exception—this Pokémon can't change the zigzag pattern on its belly.

0353shup.dexEntry: Shuppet grows by feeding on dark emotions, such as vengefulness and envy, in the hearts of people. It roams through cities in search of grudges that taint people.

0354bane.dexEntry: A cursed energy permeated the stuffing of a discarded and forgotten plush doll, giving it new life as Banette. The Pokémon's energy would escape if it were to ever open its mouth.

0355dusk.dexEntry: Duskull can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. Once this Pokémon chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended victim until the break of dawn.

0356dusc.dexEntry: Dusclops's body is completely hollow—there is nothing at all inside. It is said that its body is like a black hole. This Pokémon will absorb anything into its body, but nothing will ever come back out.

0357trop.dexEntry: Children of the southern tropics eat as snacks the fruit that grows in bunches around the neck of Tropius. This Pokémon flies by flapping the leaves on its back as if they were wings.

0358chim.dexEntry: Chimecho makes its cries echo inside its hollow body. When this Pokémon becomes enraged, its cries result in ultrasonic waves that have the power to knock foes flying.

0359abso.dexEntry: Although it's said to bring disaster, in actuality, this Pokémon possesses a calm disposition and warns people of any crises that loom.

0360wyna.dexEntry: Wynaut can always be seen with a big, happy smile on its face. Look at its tail to determine if it is angry. When angered, this Pokémon will be slapping the ground with its tail.

0361snor.dexEntry: It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as -150 degrees Fahrenheit.

0362glal.dexEntry: Its prey is instantaneously frozen stiff by the cold air it exhales from its huge mouth. While they're in that frozen state, it gobbles them up.

0363sphe.dexEntry: Spheal is much faster rolling than walking to get around. When groups of this Pokémon eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this, their mealtimes are noisy.

0364seal.dexEntry: Sealeo has the habit of always juggling on the tip of its nose anything it sees for the first time. This Pokémon occasionally entertains itself by balancing and rolling a <<0363sphe>> on its nose.

0365walr.dexEntry: Walrein's two massively developed tusks can totally shatter blocks of ice weighing 10 tons with one blow. This Pokémon's thick coat of blubber insulates it from subzero temperatures.

0366clam.dexEntry: Clamperl grows while being protected by its rock-hard shell. When its body becomes too large to fit inside the shell, it is sure evidence that this Pokémon is getting close to evolution.

0367hunt.dexEntry: Huntail's tail is shaped like a fish. It uses the tail to attract prey, then swallows the prey whole with its large, gaping mouth. This Pokémon swims by wiggling its slender body like a snake.

0368gore.dexEntry: Gorebyss lives in the southern seas at extreme depths. Its body is built to withstand the enormous pressure of water at incredible depths. Because of this, this Pokémon's body is unharmed by ordinary attacks.

0369reli.dexEntry: It was fortuitously discovered during a deep sea expedition. Its teeth have atrophied, so it now survives on microscopic organisms it sucks up.

0370luvd.dexEntry: If a Luvdisc is left on its own, it becomes despondent, leaving itself open to attack. That is when <<0279peli>> snatch them up.

0371bago.dexEntry: With its steel-hard stone head, it headbutts indiscriminately. This is because of the stress it feels at being unable to fly.

0372shel.dexEntry: They lurk deep within caves—motionless, neither eating nor drinking. Why they don't die is not known.

0373sala.dexEntry: It flies around on its wings, which have grown in at last. In its happiness, it gushes hot flames, burning up the fields it passes over.

0374beld.dexEntry: Its cells are all magnets. It uses magnetism to communicate with others of its kind.

0375meta.dexEntry: When two <<0374beld>> link together, their psychic power is doubled. Their intelligence, however, remains unchanged.

0376meta.dexEntry: It firmly pins its prey using its four claws and large body. Then the teeth in the mouth on its stomach chew the prey to bits.

0377regi.dexEntry: Regirock was sealed away by people long ago. If this Pokémon's body is damaged in battle, it is said to seek out suitable rocks on its own to repair itself.

0378regi.dexEntry: Regice cloaks itself with frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit. Things will freeze solid just by going near this Pokémon. Its icy body is so cold, it will not melt even if it is immersed in magma.

0379regi.dexEntry: Registeel has a body that is harder than any kind of metal. Its body is apparently hollow. No one has any idea what this Pokémon eats.

0380lati.dexEntry: Latias is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The Pokémon enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

0381lati.dexEntry: Latios has the ability to make others see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This Pokémon is intelligent and understands human speech.

0382kyog.dexEntry: Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.

0383grou.dexEntry: Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can cause magma to erupt and expand the landmass of the world.

0384rayq.dexEntry: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between <<0382kyog>> and <<0383grou>>.

0385jira.dexEntry: Jirachi will awaken from its sleep of a thousand years if you sing to it in a voice of purity. It is said to make true any wish that people desire.

0387turt.dexEntry: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.

0388grot.dexEntry: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

0389tort.dexEntry: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

0390chim.dexEntry: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can't extinguish the fire.

0391monf.dexEntry: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

0392infe.dexEntry: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.

0393pipl.dexEntry: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

0394prin.dexEntry: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

0395empo.dexEntry: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

0396star.dexEntry: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.

0397star.dexEntry: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.

0398star.dexEntry: The muscles in its wings and legs are strong. It can easily fly while gripping a small Pokémon.

0399bido.dexEntry: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

0400biba.dexEntry: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

0401kric.dexEntry: It chats with others using the sounds of its colliding antennae. These sounds are fall hallmarks.

0402kric.dexEntry: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.

0403shin.dexEntry: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

0404luxi.dexEntry: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.

0405luxr.dexEntry: When its eyes gleam gold, it can spot hiding prey—even those taking shelter behind a wall.

0406bude.dexEntry: When it feels the sun's warm touch, it opens its bud to release pollen. It lives alongside clear pools.

0407rose.dexEntry: Luring prey with a sweet scent, it uses poison whips on its arms to poison, bind, and finish off the prey.

0408cran.dexEntry: It lived in jungles around a hundred million years ago. It used its skillful headbutts to combat <<0142aero>>.

0409ramp.dexEntry: The result of repeated headbutts is a skull grown thick and hard. However, its brain has shrunk in size compared with <<0408cran>>'s.

0410shie.dexEntry: This Pokémon lived in primeval jungles. Few enemies would have been willing to square off against its heavily armored face, so it's thought.

0411bast.dexEntry: It lived in the same environments as <<0409ramp>>. Their fossils have been found together—seemingly from after they'd fought to the finish.

0412burm.dexEntry: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

0413worm.dexEntry: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

0414moth.dexEntry: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the <<0415comb>> hive.

0415comb.dexEntry: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers honey from flowers to please <<0416vesp>>.

0416vesp.dexEntry: It houses its colony in cells in its body and releases various pheromones to make those grubs do its bidding.

0417pach.dexEntry: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

0418buiz.dexEntry: It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw. When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.

0419floa.dexEntry: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.

0420cher.dexEntry: It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.

0421cher.dexEntry: If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun's rays with its whole body.

0424ambi.dexEntry: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

0425drif.dexEntry: Stories go that it grabs the hands of small children and drags them away to the afterlife. It dislikes heavy children.

0426drif.dexEntry: There was once an incident in which a man took a trip riding a Drifblim, only to go missing.

0427bune.dexEntry: Its ears are always rolled up. They can be forcefully extended to shatter even a large boulder.

0428lopu.dexEntry: Extremely cautious, it quickly bounds off when it senses danger.

0429mism.dexEntry: Mismagius have been known to cast spells to make people fall in love, so some people search for this Pokémon as if their life depended on it.

0430honc.dexEntry: A single cry from this nocturnal Pokémon, and more than a hundred of its <<0198murk>> cronies will assemble.

0431glam.dexEntry: When it's happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

0432puru.dexEntry: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.

0433chin.dexEntry: Each time it hops, it makes a ringing sound. It deafens foes by emitting high-frequency cries.

0434stun.dexEntry: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

0435skun.dexEntry: It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester.

0436bron.dexEntry: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor's back contained a mysterious power.

0437bron.dexEntry: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

0438bons.dexEntry: It does not deal well with water, so it lives in dry locales. Since its surroundings tend to lack greenery, it stands out noticeably.

0439mime.dexEntry: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

0440happ.dexEntry: It carries a round white rock in its belly pouch. If it gets along well with someone, it will sometimes give that person the rock.

0441chat.dexEntry: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

0442spir.dexEntry: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.

0443gibl.dexEntry: It lives in caves warmed by geothermal heat. Even so, when the weather gets cold, it will huddle close with others of its kind.

0444gabi.dexEntry: In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.

0445garc.dexEntry: It can fly at speeds rivaling jet planes. It dives into flocks of bird Pokémon and gulps the entire flock down whole.

0446munc.dexEntry: When it finds something that looks like it might be edible, it goes right ahead and swallows it whole. That's why it gets fatter day by day.

0447riol.dexEntry: It can discern the physical and emotional states of people, Pokémon, and other natural things from the shape of their aura waves.

0448luca.dexEntry: Not only does it perceive auras, but it has also gained the power to control them. It employs them in battle.

0449hipp.dexEntry: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.

0450hipp.dexEntry: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

0451skor.dexEntry: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.

0452drap.dexEntry: It takes pride in its strength. Even though it can tear foes apart, it finishes them off with powerful poison.

0453croa.dexEntry: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

0454toxi.dexEntry: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

0455carn.dexEntry: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

0456finn.dexEntry: Its double tail fins propel its energetic jumps. When it breaks the surface of the sea, <<0278wing>> swoop down to grab it on the fly.

0457lumi.dexEntry: This deep-sea Pokémon lives at the bottom of the sea. Its fins haul it over the seabed in search of its favorite food—<<0121star>>.

0458mant.dexEntry: The pattern on its back varies by region. It often swims in a school of <<0223remo>>.

0459snov.dexEntry: In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of frozen treats around its belly.

0460abom.dexEntry: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

0461weav.dexEntry: They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.

0462magn.dexEntry: As it zooms through the sky, this Pokémon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin, while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.

0463lick.dexEntry: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.

0464rhyp.dexEntry: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. <<0074geod>> are shot at rare times.

0465tang.dexEntry: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.

0466elec.dexEntry: It pushes the tips of its tails against its foes and then lets loose a high-voltage current. Its foes are burned to a crisp in an instant.

0467magm.dexEntry: From its arm, it launches fireballs hotter than 3,500 degrees Fahrenheit. Its arm starts to melt when it fires a whole barrage.

0468toge.dexEntry: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.

0469yanm.dexEntry: It prefers to battle by biting apart foes' heads instantly while flying by at high speed.

0470leaf.dexEntry: The younger they are, the more they smell like fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on the odor of fallen leaves.

0471glac.dexEntry: It can control its body temperature at will. This enables it to freeze the moisture in the atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.

0472glis.dexEntry: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

0473mamo.dexEntry: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

0474pory.dexEntry: In order to create a more advanced Pokémon, an additional program was installed, but apparently it contained a defect that makes it move oddly.

0475gall.dexEntry: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.

0476prob.dexEntry: The main body controls three mobile units called Mini-Noses, which it maneuvers to catch prey.

0477dusk.dexEntry: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.

0478fros.dexEntry: The soul of a woman lost on a snowy mountain possessed an icicle, becoming this Pokémon. The food it most relishes is the souls of men.

0479roto.dexEntry: Research continues on this Pokémon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.

0480uxie.dexEntry: Known as "The Being of Knowledge". It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

0481mesp.dexEntry: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake's surface.

0482azel.dexEntry: Known as "The Being of Willpower". It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

0483dial.dexEntry: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

0484palk.dexEntry: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

0485heat.dexEntry: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

0486regi.dexEntry: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

0487gira.dexEntry: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.

0488cres.dexEntry: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

0489phio.dexEntry: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

0490mana.dexEntry: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.

0491dark.dexEntry: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

0492shay.dexEntry: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.

0493arce.dexEntry: According to the legends of Sinnoh, this Pokémon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.

0494vict.dexEntry: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

0495sniv.dexEntry: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.

0496serv.dexEntry: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

0497serp.dexEntry: It only gives its all against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior's noble eyes.

0498tepi.dexEntry: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

0499pign.dexEntry: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

0500embo.dexEntry: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.

0501osha.dexEntry: The scalchop on its stomach isn't just used for battle—it can be used to break open hard berries as well.

0502dewo.dexEntry: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

0504patr.dexEntry: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

0505watc.dexEntry: Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.

0506lill.dexEntry: The long fur surrounding its face functions as radar, enabling it to probe the condition of its battle opponents.

0507herd.dexEntry: This Pokémon obeys its master's orders faithfully. However, it refuses to listen to anything said by a person it doesn't respect.

0508stou.dexEntry: With this wise Pokémon, there could be no concern that it would ever attack people. Some parents even trust it to babysit.

0509purr.dexEntry: Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It attacks with sharp claws.

0510liep.dexEntry: Their beautiful form comes from the muscles they have developed. They run silently in the night.

0511pans.dexEntry: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

0512simi.dexEntry: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

0513pans.dexEntry: Very intelligent, it roasts berries before eating them. It likes to help people.

0514simi.dexEntry: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.

0515panp.dexEntry: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

0516simi.dexEntry: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

0517munn.dexEntry: This Pokémon appears before people and Pokémon who are having nightmares and eats those dreams.

0518mush.dexEntry: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.

0519pido.dexEntry: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.

0520tran.dexEntry: No matter where in the world it goes, it knows where its nest is, so it never gets separated from its Trainer.

0521unfe.dexEntry: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.

0522blit.dexEntry: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

0523zebs.dexEntry: When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

0524rogg.dexEntry: Born deep within the ground, it compares itself with similar species, such as <<0074geod>> and <<0703carb>>, to settle which has the hardest body.

0525bold.dexEntry: Its orange crystal is a mass of energy. Just one crystal fragment would provide enough fuel for a hundred dump trucks.

0526giga.dexEntry: The blasts of energy it makes from sunbeams have terrifying power. However, it's not able to fire its blasts at night or on rainy days.

0527woob.dexEntry: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

0528swoo.dexEntry: It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.

0529dril.dexEntry: By spinning its body, it can dig straight through the ground at a speed of 30 mph.

0530exca.dexEntry: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.

0531audi.dexEntry: Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.

0532timb.dexEntry: Always carrying squared logs, they help out with construction. As they grow, they carry bigger logs.

0533gurd.dexEntry: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

0534conk.dexEntry: Rather than rely on force, they master moves that utilize the centrifugal force of spinning concrete.

0535tymp.dexEntry: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans and warns others of danger.

0536palp.dexEntry: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.

0537seis.dexEntry: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.

0538thro.dexEntry: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.

0539sawk.dexEntry: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

0540sewa.dexEntry: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.

0541swad.dexEntry: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

0542leav.dexEntry: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves by using the sticky silk secreted from its mouth.

0543veni.dexEntry: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

0544whir.dexEntry: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.

0545scol.dexEntry: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

0546cott.dexEntry: When it finds others of its kind, they all stick together. When enough of them have collected, the mass resembles a cumulonimbus cloud.

0547whim.dexEntry: It rides on the wind and slips into people's homes. After it has turned a room into a cotton-filled mess, it giggles to itself and takes off.

0548peti.dexEntry: By pruning the leaves on its head with regularity, this Pokémon can be grown into a fine plump shape.

0551sand.dexEntry: It submerges itself in sand and moves as if swimming. This wise behavior keeps its enemies from finding it and maintains its temperature.

0552krok.dexEntry: They move in groups of a few individuals. A female is often the leader of the group, and the males will gather food.

0553kroo.dexEntry: Its unique faculty of sight can detect small prey more than 30 miles away, even in the midst of a sandstorm.

0556mara.dexEntry: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.

0557dweb.dexEntry: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.

0558crus.dexEntry: It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling it to carry heavy slabs for many days, even when crossing arid land.

0559scra.dexEntry: Proud of its sturdy skull, it suddenly headbutts everything, but its weight makes it unstable, too.

0560scra.dexEntry: It can smash concrete blocks with its kicking attacks. The one with the biggest crest is the group leader.

0561sigi.dexEntry: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.

0563cofa.dexEntry: Grave robbers who mistake them for real coffins and get too close end up trapped inside their bodies.

0564tirt.dexEntry: Based on studies of its skeletal structure, it can apparently dive to ocean depths of over half a mile.

0565carr.dexEntry: It constructed its sturdy shell by crunching and swallowing the hard shells or bones of its prey.

0566arch.dexEntry: To all appearances flightless, it was able to glide down from tall treetops to snag its prey.

0567arch.dexEntry: They hunted in flocks. When one Archeops had the prey cornered, another would swoop on it.

0568trub.dexEntry: Unsanitary places are what they like best. They can be spotted in Alola, often with <<0088grim>> in hot pursuit.

0569garb.dexEntry: Beware the poisonous liquid it shoots from its right arm. If even a little of it gets on you, you'll experience the effects of the unidentified toxin.

0572minc.dexEntry: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.

0573cinc.dexEntry: Cinccino's body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.

0574goth.dexEntry: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

0575goth.dexEntry: Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.

0576goth.dexEntry: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

0577solo.dexEntry: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

0578duos.dexEntry: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.

0579reun.dexEntry: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

0580duck.dexEntry: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

0581swan.dexEntry: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

0582vani.dexEntry: Born of an icicle, this Pokémon uses its frosty breath to make ice crystals, causing snow to fall.

0583vani.dexEntry: Hot days cause its body to melt. It can be restored by refreezing it, but the process leaves its body slightly warped.

0584vani.dexEntry: Each of its two heads has a brain, and when they are in agreement, it attacks its enemies by exhaling a violent blizzard.

0585deer.dexEntry: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

0586saws.dexEntry: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.

0587emol.dexEntry: It glides using its cape-like membrane. Electrical energy scatters from it, shocking its friends and foes alike.

0588karr.dexEntry: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking <<0616shel>>.

0589esca.dexEntry: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a <<0616shel>>. The steel armor protects their whole body.

0590foon.dexEntry: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.

0591amoo.dexEntry: They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.

0592fril.dexEntry: They paralyze prey with poison, then drag them down to their lairs, five miles below the surface.

0593jell.dexEntry: Its body is mostly seawater. It's said there's a castle of ships Jellicent have sunk on the seafloor.

0594alom.dexEntry: They float upon the open sea. Many water Pokémon gather in the area around Alomomola.

0595jolt.dexEntry: Since it can't generate its own electricity, it sticks onto large-bodied Pokémon and absorbs static electricity.

0596galv.dexEntry: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.

0597ferr.dexEntry: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.

0598ferr.dexEntry: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

0599klin.dexEntry: Interlocking two bodies and spinning around generates the energy they need to live.

0600klan.dexEntry: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

0601klin.dexEntry: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.

0602tyna.dexEntry: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

0603eele.dexEntry: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

0604eele.dexEntry: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

0605elgy.dexEntry: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent's brain, causing unendurable headaches.

0606behe.dexEntry: Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three fingers, but those patterns haven't been decoded.

0607litw.dexEntry: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

0608lamp.dexEntry: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.

0609chan.dexEntry: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.

0610axew.dexEntry: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.

0611frax.dexEntry: Their tusks can shatter rocks. Territory battles between Fraxure can be intensely violent.

0612haxo.dexEntry: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

0613cubc.dexEntry: Their snot is a barometer of health. When healthy, their snot is sticky and the power of their ice moves increases.

0614bear.dexEntry: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.

0615cryo.dexEntry: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148 degrees Fahrenheit.

0616shel.dexEntry: When it and <<0588karr>> are together, and both receive electrical stimulation, they both evolve.

0617acce.dexEntry: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

0619mien.dexEntry: It takes pride in the speed at which it can use moves. What it loses in power, it makes up for in quantity.

0620mien.dexEntry: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

0621drud.dexEntry: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.

0622gole.dexEntry: Ancient science fashioned this Pokémon from clay. It's been active for thousands of years.

0623golu.dexEntry: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

0624pawn.dexEntry: Blades comprise this Pokémon's entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

0625bish.dexEntry: This pitiless Pokémon commands a group of <<0624pawn>> to hound prey into immobility. It then moves in to finish the prey off.

0626bouf.dexEntry: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

0627ruff.dexEntry: They pick fights indiscriminately. They grow stronger and more powerful each time they faint or are injured.

0629vull.dexEntry: It can't fly yet and must wait until its wings have developed more. Since it's still at a playful age, it hops around friskily.

0630mand.dexEntry: It circles in the sky, keeping a keen eye out for Pokémon in a weakened state. Its choicest food is <<0104cubo>>.

0631heat.dexEntry: Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues, they burn through <<0632dura>>'s steel bodies and consume their insides.

0632dura.dexEntry: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from <<0631heat>>.

0633dein.dexEntry: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.

0634zwei.dexEntry: The two heads do not get along. Whichever head eats more than the other gets to be the leader.

0635hydr.dexEntry: The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.

0636larv.dexEntry: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.

0637volc.dexEntry: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona's fire provided a replacement for the sun.

0638coba.dexEntry: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.

0639terr.dexEntry: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.

0640viri.dexEntry: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.

0641torn.dexEntry: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

0642thun.dexEntry: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

0643resh.dexEntry: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.

0644zekr.dexEntry: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

0645land.dexEntry: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields".

0646kyur.dexEntry: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

0647keld.dexEntry: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.

0648melo.dexEntry: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

0649gene.dexEntry: This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.

0650ches.dexEntry: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

0651quil.dexEntry: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators' attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.

0652ches.dexEntry: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

0653fenn.dexEntry: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

0654brai.dexEntry: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

0655delp.dexEntry: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

0656froa.dexEntry: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

0657frog.dexEntry: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute's time.

0658gren.dexEntry: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

0659bunn.dexEntry: They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.

0660digg.dexEntry: With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.

0661flet.dexEntry: This amiable Pokémon is easy to train. But when battle is joined, it shows its ferocious side.

0662flet.dexEntry: From its beak, it fires embers at its prey. Once it has caught them, it grills them at high heat before feasting upon them.

0663talo.dexEntry: Its favorite foods are <<0278wing>> and <<0731piki>>. It attacks with a powerful kick and grasps them firmly in its talons.

0664scat.dexEntry: When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.

0665spew.dexEntry: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.

0666vivi.dexEntry: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.

0667litl.dexEntry: They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick to fight.

0668pyro.dexEntry: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride's cubs.

0669flab.dexEntry: It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. The flower Flabébé holds is most likely part of its body.

0670floe.dexEntry: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.

0671flor.dexEntry: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.

0672skid.dexEntry: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn't need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.

0673gogo.dexEntry: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.

0674panc.dexEntry: It grows up imitating the behavior of <<0675pang>>, which it looks up to as a leader.

0675pang.dexEntry: It boasts superb physical strength. Those who wish to become Pangoro's Trainer have no choice but to converse with their fists.

0676furf.dexEntry: Historically, in the Kalos region, these Pokémon were the designated guardians of the king.

0677espu.dexEntry: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.

0678meow.dexEntry: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.

0679hone.dexEntry: If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.

0680doub.dexEntry: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.

0681aegi.dexEntry: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.

0682spri.dexEntry: It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.

0683arom.dexEntry: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.

0684swir.dexEntry: Because it eats nothing but sweets, its fur is as sticky sweet as cotton candy.

0685slur.dexEntry: Its sense of smell is 100 million times better than a human's, so even the faintest scent tells it about everything in the area. It's like it can see with its nose!

0686inka.dexEntry: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.

0687mala.dexEntry: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.

0688bina.dexEntry: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.

0689barb.dexEntry: Barbaracle's legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head's orders.

0690skre.dexEntry: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.

0691drag.dexEntry: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.

0692clau.dexEntry: Through controlled explosions of internal gas, it can expel water like a pistol shot. At close distances, it can shatter rock.

0693claw.dexEntry: By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.

0694heli.dexEntry: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.

0695heli.dexEntry: It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.

0696tyru.dexEntry: Its immense jaws have enough destructive force that it can chew up an automobile. It lived 100 million years ago.

0697tyra.dexEntry: Nothing could stop this Pokémon 100 million years ago, so it behaved like a king.

0698amau.dexEntry: This ancient Pokémon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.
