0699auro.dexEntry: The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.

0700sylv.dexEntry: Its ribbonlike feelers give off an aura that weakens hostility in its prey, causing them to let down their guard. Then it attacks.

0701hawl.dexEntry: With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.

0702dede.dexEntry: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.

0703carb.dexEntry: Born from the high temperatures and pressures deep underground, it defends itself by firing beams from the jewel part of its body.

0704goom.dexEntry: The weakest of all Dragon-type Pokémon, it's unable to breathe if its skin dries out, so it sticks to shady places.

0707klef.dexEntry: It inserts its horn into chinks in metal, absorbing metal ions. For some reason, it collects keys.

0708phan.dexEntry: These Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died in the forest. Their cries sound like eerie screams.

0709trev.dexEntry: This Pokémon is said to devour anyone daring to ravage the forest. To the creatures dwelling in the forest, it offers great kindness.

0710pump.dexEntry: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

0711gour.dexEntry: Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.

0712berg.dexEntry: Using air of -150 degrees Fahrenheit, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.

0714noib.dexEntry: They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.

0715noiv.dexEntry: They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.

0716xern.dexEntry: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

0717yvel.dexEntry: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

0719dian.dexEntry: A sudden transformation of <<0703carb>>, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

0720hoop.dexEntry: In its true form, it possess a huge amount of power. Legends of its avarice tell how it once carried off an entire castle to gain the treasure hidden within.

0721volc.dexEntry: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

0722rowl.dexEntry: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

0723dart.dexEntry: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

0725litt.dexEntry: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

0726torr.dexEntry: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.

0727inci.dexEntry: This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it's not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer's orders with complete nonchalance.

0728popp.dexEntry: This Pokémon can control water bubbles. It practices diligently so it can learn to make big bubbles.

0729brio.dexEntry: It cares deeply for its companions. When its Trainer is feeling down, it performs a cheery dance to try and help.

0730prim.dexEntry: Its singing voice is its chief weapon in battle. This Pokémon's Trainer must prioritize the daily maintenance of its throat at all costs.

0731piki.dexEntry: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses the holes for food storage and for nesting.

0732trum.dexEntry: It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.

0733touc.dexEntry: When it battles, its beak heats up. The temperature can easily exceed 212 degrees Fahrenheit, causing severe burns when it hits.

0734yung.dexEntry: With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. It did not originally live in Alola but was imported from another region.

0735gums.dexEntry: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location... but it's always snoozing by nightfall.

0736grub.dexEntry: Its strong jaw enables it to scrape trees and slurp out the sap. It normally lives underground.

0737char.dexEntry: Its body is capable of storing electricity. On camping trips, people are grateful to have one around.

0738vika.dexEntry: It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening. It concentrates electrical energy within its large jaws and uses it to zap its enemies.

0739crab.dexEntry: It punches so much, its pincers often come off from overuse, but they grow back quickly. What little meat they contain is rich and delicious.

0740crab.dexEntry: It just throws punches indiscriminately. In times of desperation, it can lop off its own pincers and fire them like rockets.

0742cuti.dexEntry: It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because it's able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.

0743ribo.dexEntry: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.

0744rock.dexEntry: This Pokémon has lived with people since times long ago. It can sense when its Trainer is in the dumps and will stick close by its Trainer's side.

0746wish.dexEntry: When it's in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies.

0747mare.dexEntry: It's found crawling on beaches and seafloors. The coral that grows on <<0222cors>>'s head is as good as a five-star banquet to this Pokémon.

0748toxa.dexEntry: Those attacked by Toxapex's poison will suffer intense pain for three days and three nights. Post-recovery, there will be some aftereffects.

0749mudb.dexEntry: The mud stuck to Mudbray's hooves enhances its grip and its powerful running gait.

0750muds.dexEntry: It spits a mud that provides resistance to both wind and rain, so the walls of old houses were often coated with it.

0751dewp.dexEntry: When it comes across enemies or potential prey, this Pokémon smashes its water-bubble-covered head into them.

0752araq.dexEntry: Despite what its appearance suggests, it cares for others. If it finds vulnerable, weak Pokémon, it protectively brings them into its water bubble.

0753foma.dexEntry: During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light. When night falls, it walks around looking for a safer place to sleep.

0754lura.dexEntry: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis's vivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this work and treat it as their hobby.

0755more.dexEntry: As it drowses the day away, it nourishes itself by sucking from tree roots. It wakens at the fall of night, wandering off in search of a new tree.

0756shii.dexEntry: It emits flickering spores that cause drowsiness. When its prey succumb to sleep, this Pokémon feeds on them by sucking in their energy.

0757sala.dexEntry: It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.

0758sala.dexEntry: For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male <<0757sala>> that it lives with.

0759stuf.dexEntry: A touch from anyone except a known friend sends it into a surging frenzy. It's an incredibly dangerous Pokémon.

0760bewe.dexEntry: This Pokémon has the habit of hugging its companions. Many Trainers have left this world after their spines were squashed by its hug.

0761boun.dexEntry: A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed whole by <<0733touc>> lured by that wafting deliciousness.

0762stee.dexEntry: The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. These are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.

0763tsar.dexEntry: Its long, striking legs aren't just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.

0764comf.dexEntry: Baths prepared with the flowers from its vine have a relaxing effect, so this Pokémon is a hit with many people.

0765oran.dexEntry: Known for its extreme intelligence, this Pokémon will look down on inexperienced Trainers, so it's best suited to veteran Trainers.

0766pass.dexEntry: They battle with hard berries for weapons. Their techniques are passed from the boss to the group, generation upon generation.

0767wimp.dexEntry: This Pokémon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.

0768goli.dexEntry: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater—or even air—right in two.

0769sand.dexEntry: It takes control of anyone who puts a hand in its mouth. And so it adds to the accumulation of its sand-mound body.

0770palo.dexEntry: Buried beneath the castle are masses of dried-up bones from those whose vitality it has drained.

0771pyuk.dexEntry: It lives in shallow seas, such as areas near a beach. It can eject its internal organs, which it uses to engulf its prey or battle enemies.

0772type.dexEntry: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This Pokémon has some hidden special power.

0773silv.dexEntry: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This Pokémon is capable of changing its type, a flexibility that is well displayed in battle.

0775koma.dexEntry: It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.

0776turt.dexEntry: It gushes fire and poisonous gases from its nostrils. Its dung is an explosive substance and can be put to various uses.

0777toge.dexEntry: The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokémon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.

0778mimi.dexEntry: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.

0779brux.dexEntry: It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then grinds them to mush with its strong teeth. Even <<0090shel>>'s shell is no match for it.

0780dram.dexEntry: It has a compassionate personality, but if it is angered, it completely destroys its surroundings with its intense breath.

0781dhel.dexEntry: The soul of seaweed adrift in the waves became reborn as this Pokémon. It maintains itself with new infusions of seabed detritus and seaweed.

0782jang.dexEntry: It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.

0783haka.dexEntry: It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.

0784komm.dexEntry: When it spots enemies, it threatens them by jingling the scales on its tail. Weak opponents will crack and flee in panic.

0785tapu.dexEntry: This guardian deity of Melemele is brimming with curiosity. It summons thunderclouds and stores their lightning inside its body.

0786tapu.dexEntry: This guardian deity of Akala is guilelessly cruel. The fragrant aroma of flowers is the source of its energy.

0787tapu.dexEntry: The guardian deity of Ula'ula is a lazy Pokémon. It commands plants to immobilize its foes and then deals them a savage blow with its horns.

0788tapu.dexEntry: The guardian deity of Poni, it can control water. People say it can create pure water that will wash away any uncleanness.

0789cosm.dexEntry: In ages past, it was called the child of the stars. It's said to be a Pokémon from another world, but no specific details are known.

0790cosm.dexEntry: There's something accumulating around the black core within its hard shell. People think this Pokémon may come from another world.

0791solg.dexEntry: It is said to live in another world. The intense light it radiates from the surface of its body can make the darkest of nights light up like midday.

0792luna.dexEntry: Said to live in another world, this Pokémon devours light, drawing the moonless dark veil of night over the brightness of day.

0793nihi.dexEntry: One of several mysterious Ultra Beasts. People on the street report observing those infested by it suddenly becoming violent.

0794buzz.dexEntry: This Ultra Beast appeared from another world. It shows off its body, but whether that display is a boast or a threat remains unclear.

0795pher.dexEntry: One of the dangerous Ultra Beasts, it has been spotted running across the land at terrific speeds.

0796xurk.dexEntry: One of the mysterious life-forms known as Ultra Beasts. Astonishing electric shocks emanate from its entire body, according to witnesses.

0797cele.dexEntry: One kind of Ultra Beast. Witnesses have seen it burn down a forest by expelling gas from its two arms.

0798kart.dexEntry: This Ultra Beast came from the Ultra Wormhole. It seems not to attack enemies on its own, but its sharp body is a dangerous weapon in itself.

0799guzz.dexEntry: It has gobbled mountains and swallowed whole buildings, according to reports. It's one of the Ultra Beasts.

0801mage.dexEntry: This artificial Pokémon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.

0802mars.dexEntry: Able to conceal itself in shadows, it never appears before humans, so its very existence was the stuff of myth.

0803poip.dexEntry: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.

0804naga.dexEntry: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.

0805stak.dexEntry: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

0806blac.dexEntry: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It's apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

0807zera.dexEntry: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they'll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

0808melt.dexEntry: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

0809melm.dexEntry: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.

0810groo.dexEntry: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

0811thwa.dexEntry: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.

0812rill.dexEntry: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

0813scor.dexEntry: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon’s body. Once that happens, it’s ready to fight at full power.

0814rabo.dexEntry: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it from the cold and enables it to use hotter fire moves.

0815cind.dexEntry: It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched.

0816sobb.dexEntry: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won’t be able to resist weeping.

0817driz.dexEntry: A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.

0818inte.dexEntry: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

0819skwo.dexEntry: Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.

0820gree.dexEntry: It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn’t notice the loss.

0821rook.dexEntry: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.

0822corv.dexEntry: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.

0823corv.dexEntry: This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.

0824blip.dexEntry: A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn’t.

0825dott.dexEntry: It barely moves, but it’s still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.

0826orbe.dexEntry: It’s famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.

0827nick.dexEntry: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.

0828thie.dexEntry: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.

0829goss.dexEntry: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

0830elde.dexEntry: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

0831wool.dexEntry: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

0832dubw.dexEntry: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You’ll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

0833chew.dexEntry: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.

0834dred.dexEntry: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

0835yamp.dexEntry: This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.

0836bolt.dexEntry: This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.

0837roly.dexEntry: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.

0838cark.dexEntry: It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokémon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region.

0839coal.dexEntry: It’s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

0840appl.dexEntry: It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it’s just an apple and nothing more.

0841flap.dexEntry: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.

0842appl.dexEntry: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on.

0843sili.dexEntry: As it digs, it swallows sand and stores it in its neck pouch. The pouch can hold more than 17 pounds of sand.

0844sand.dexEntry: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.

0845cram.dexEntry: It’s so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it’s battling midfight.

0846arro.dexEntry: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It’s very proud of that jaw.

0847barr.dexEntry: This Pokémon has a jaw that’s as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda’s flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.

0848toxe.dexEntry: It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows.

0850sizz.dexEntry: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

0851cent.dexEntry: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

0852clob.dexEntry: It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

0853grap.dexEntry: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.

0854sini.dexEntry: This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.

0855polt.dexEntry: This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.

0856hate.dexEntry: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures’ emotions. If you don’t have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.

0857hatt.dexEntry: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.

0858hatt.dexEntry: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.

0859impi.dexEntry: Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.

0860morg.dexEntry: When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, its trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.

0861grim.dexEntry: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even <<0068mach>>.

0862obst.dexEntry: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout—this move is known as Obstruct.

0863perr.dexEntry: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.

0864curs.dexEntry: Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokémon’s core spirit.

0865sirf.dexEntry: Only <<0083farf>> that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon’s leek withers, it will retire from combat.

0866mrri.dexEntry: It's highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.

0867rune.dexEntry: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.

0868milc.dexEntry: This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.

0870fali.dexEntry: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass's orders are absolute.

0871pinc.dexEntry: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.

0872snom.dexEntry: It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.

0873fros.dexEntry: Icy scales fall from its wings like snow as it flies over fields and mountains. The temperature of its wings is less than −290 degrees Fahrenheit.

0874ston.dexEntry: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun’s descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.

0875eisc.dexEntry: It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.

0877morp.dexEntry: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It's also generating electricity.

0878cufa.dexEntry: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It's also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.

0879copp.dexEntry: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.

0880drac.dexEntry: In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.

0881arct.dexEntry: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.

0882drac.dexEntry: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.

0883arct.dexEntry: Though it's able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.

0884dura.dexEntry: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

0885dree.dexEntry: After being reborn as a ghost Pokémon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.

0886drak.dexEntry: It's capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside <<0885dree>> and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.

0887drag.dexEntry: When it isn't battling, it keeps <<0885dree>> in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the <<0885dree>> like supersonic missiles.

0888zaci.dexEntry: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokémon absorbs metal particles, transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.

0889zama.dexEntry: In times past, it worked together with a king of the people to save the Galar region. It absorbs metal that it then uses in battle.

0890eter.dexEntry: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.

0891kubf.dexEntry: Kubfu trains hard to perfect its moves. The moves it masters will determine which form it takes when it evolves.

0893zaru.dexEntry: Within dense forests, this Pokémon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It's incredibly aggressive, and the other Pokémon of the forest fear it.

0894regi.dexEntry: This Pokemon is a cluster of electrical energy. It's said that removing the rings on Regieleki's body will unleash the Pokémon's latent power.

0895regi.dexEntry: An academic theory proposes that Regidrago's arms were once the head of an ancient dragon. The theory remains unproven.

0896glas.dexEntry: Glastrier emits intense cold from its hooves. It's also a belligerent Pokémon—anything it wants, it takes by force.

0897spec.dexEntry: It probes its surroundings with all its senses save one—it doesn't use its sense of sight. Spectrier's kicks are said to separate soul from body.

0898caly.dexEntry: Calyrex is a merciful Pokémon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.

0899wyrd.dexEntry: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.

0900klea.dexEntry: A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokémon in the wilds, one's only recourse is to flee.

0901ursa.dexEntry: I believe it was Hisui's swampy terrain that gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.

0902basc.dexEntry: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui's rivers is Basculegion's equal.

0903snea.dexEntry: Because of Sneasler's virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.

0904over.dexEntry: Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname 'sea fiend'. It slurps up poison to nourish itself.

0905enam.dexEntry: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokémon's love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

0906spri.dexEntry: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

0907flor.dexEntry: The hardness of Floragato's fur depends on the Pokémon's mood. When Floragato is prepared to battle, its fur becomes pointed and sharp.

0908meow.dexEntry: This Pokémon uses the reflective fur lining its cape to camouflage the stem of its flower, creating the illusion that the flower is floating.

0909fuec.dexEntry: It lies on warm rocks and uses the heat absorbed by its square-shaped scales to create fire energy.

0910croc.dexEntry: The combination of Crocalor’s fire energy and overflowing vitality has caused an egg-shaped fireball to appear on the Pokémon’s head.

0911skel.dexEntry: The fiery bird changes shape when Skeledirge sings. Rumor has it that the bird was born when the fireball on Skeledirge’s head gained a soul.

0912quax.dexEntry: This Pokémon migrated to Paldea from distant lands long ago. The gel secreted by its feathers repels water and grime.

0913quax.dexEntry: These Pokémon constantly run through shallow waters to train their legs, then compete with each other to see which of them kicks most gracefully.

0914quaq.dexEntry: A single kick from a Quaquaval can send a truck rolling. This Pokémon uses its powerful legs to perform striking dances from far-off lands.

0915lech.dexEntry: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn't use it for anything other than foraging.

0916oink.dexEntry: Oinkologne is proud of its fine, glossy skin. It emits a concentrated scent from the tip of its tail.

0917taro.dexEntry: The ball of threads wrapped around its body is elastic enough to deflect the scythes of <<0123scyt>>, this Pokémon's natural ennemy.

0918spid.dexEntry: It clings to branches and ceilings using its threads and moves without a sound. It takes out its prey before the prey even notices it.

0919nymb.dexEntry: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it’s in a tough spot, this Pokémon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.

0920loki.dexEntry: When it decides to fight all out, it stands on its previously folded legs to enter Showdown Mode. It neutralizes its enemies in short order.

0921pawm.dexEntry: It has underdeveloped electric sacs on its cheeks. These sacs can produce electricity only if Pawmi rubs them furiously with the pads on its forepaws.

0922pawm.dexEntry: When its group is attacked, Pawmo is the first to leap into battle, defeating enemies with a fighting technique that utilizes electric shocks.

0923pawm.dexEntry: This Pokémon normally is slow to react, but once it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies with lightning-fast movements.

0924tand.dexEntry: Exhibiting great teamwork, they use their incisors to cut pieces out of any material that might be useful for a nest, then make off with them.

0925maus.dexEntry: They build huge nests with many rooms that are used for different purposes, such as eating and sleeping.

0926fido.dexEntry: This Pokémon is smooth and moist to the touch. Yeast in Fidough’s breath induces fermentation in the Pokémon’s vicinity.

0927dach.dexEntry: The pleasant aroma that emanates from this Pokémon's body helps wheat grow, so Dachsbun has been treasured by farming villages.

0928smol.dexEntry: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

0929doll.dexEntry: Dolliv shares its tasty, fresh-scented oil with others. This species has coexisted with humans since times long gone.

0930arbo.dexEntry: This calm Pokémon is very compassionate. It will share its delicious, nutrient-rich oil with weakened Pokémon.

0931squa.dexEntry: These Pokémon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.

0932nacl.dexEntry: It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days, as they would share precious salt.

0933nacl.dexEntry: This Pokémon dry cures its prey by spraying salt over them. The curing process steals away the water in the prey's body.

0934garg.dexEntry: Garganacl will rub its fingertips together and sprinkle injured Pokémon with salt. Even severe wounds will promptly heal afterward.

0935char.dexEntry: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Carchadet will battle even tough opponents.

0936arma.dexEntry: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokémon is incredibly loyal.

0937ceru.dexEntry: The fiery blades on its arms burn fiercely with the lingering resentment of a sword wielder who fell before accomplishing their goal.

0938tadb.dexEntry: Tadbulb shakes its tail to generate electricity. If it senses danger, it will make its head blink on and off to alert its allies.

0939bell.dexEntry: When this Pokémon expands and contracts its wobbly body, the belly-button dynamo in its stomach produces a huge amount of electricity.

0940watt.dexEntry: When its wings catch the wind, the bones within produce electricity. This Pokémon dives into the ocean, catching prey by electrocuting them.

0941kilo.dexEntry: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.

0942masc.dexEntry: It always scowls in an attempt to make opponents take it seriously, but even crying children will burst into laughter when they see Maschiff's face.

0943mabo.dexEntry: This Pokémon can store energy in its large dewlap. Mabosstiff unleashes this energy all at once to blow away enemies.

0944shro.dexEntry: Though usually a mellow Pokémon, it will sink its sharp, poison-soaked front teeth into any that anger it, causing paralysis in the object of its fire.

0945graf.dexEntry: The color of the poisonous saliva depends on what the Pokémon eats. Grafaiai covers its fingers in its saliva and draws patterns on trees in forests.

0946bram.dexEntry: A soul unable to move on to the afterlife was blown around by the wind until it got tangled up with dried grass and became a Pokémon.

0947bram.dexEntry: It will open the branches of its head to envelop its prey. Once it absorbs all the life energy it needs, it expels the prey and discards it.

0948toed.dexEntry: Toedscool lives in muggy forests. The flaps that fall from its body are chewy and very delicious.

0949toed.dexEntry: These Pokémon gather into groups and form colonies deep within forests. They absolutely hate it when strangers approach.

0950klaw.dexEntry: Klawf hangs upside-down from cliffs, waiting for prey. But Klawf can’t remain in this position for long because its blood rushes to its head.

0951caps.dexEntry: The more sunlight this Pokémon bathes in, the more spicy chemicals are produced by its body, and thus the spicier its moves become.

0952scov.dexEntry: The red head converts spicy chemicals into fire energy and blasts the surrounding area with a super spicy stream of flame.

0953rell.dexEntry: This Pokémon creates a mud ball by mixing sand and dirt with psychic energy. It treasures its mud ball more than its own life.

0954rabs.dexEntry: The body that supports the ball barely moves. Therefore, it is thought that the true body of this Pokémon is actually inside the ball.

0955flit.dexEntry: Flittle's toes levitate about an inch above the ground because of the psychic power emitted from the frills on the Pokémon's belly.

0956espa.dexEntry: It immobilizes opponents by bathing them in psychic power from its large eyes. Despite its appearance, it has a vicious temperament.

0957tink.dexEntry: It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon that eat metal.

0958tink.dexEntry: This Pokémon will attack groups of <<0624pawn>> and <<0625bish>>, gathering metal from them in order to create a large and sturdy hammer.

0959tink.dexEntry: This intelligent Pokémon has a very daring disposition. It knocks rocks into the sky with its hammer, aiming for flying <<0823corv>>.

0960wigl.dexEntry: This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a <<0976velu>> just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.

0961wugt.dexEntry: It has a vicious temperament, contrary to what its appearance may suggest. It wraps its long bodies around prey, then drags the prey into its den.

0962bomb.dexEntry: It gathers things up in an apron made from shed feathers added to the Pokémon's chest feathers, then drops those things from high places for fun.

0963fini.dexEntry: It likes playing with others of its kind using the water ring on its tail. It uses ultrasonic waves to sense the emotions of other living creatures.

0964pala.dexEntry: This Pokémon changes its appearance if it hears its allies calling for help. Palafin will never show anybody its moment of transformation.

0965varo.dexEntry: It is said that this Pokémon was born when an unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.

0966reva.dexEntry: It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders— now numbering eight—to generate energy.

0967cycl.dexEntry: Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.

0968orth.dexEntry: When attacked, this Pokémon will wield the tendrils on its body like fists and pelt the opponent with a storm of punches.

0969glim.dexEntry: It absorbs nutrients from cave walls. The petals it wears are made of crystallized poison.

0970glim.dexEntry: When this Pokémon detects danger, it will open up its crystalline petals and fire beams from its conical body.

0971grea.dexEntry: It is said that a dog Pokémon that died in the wild without ever interacting with a human was reborn as this Pokémon.

0972houn.dexEntry: Houndstone spends most of its time sleeping in graveyards. Among all the dog Pokémon, this one is most loyal to its master.

0973flam.dexEntry: This Pokémon apparently ties the base of its neck into a knot so that energy stored in its belly does not escape from its beak.

0974ceto.dexEntry: This species left the ocean and began living on land a very long time ago. It seems to be closely related to <<0320wail>>.

0975ceti.dexEntry: This Pokémon wanders around snowy, icy areas. It protects its body with powerful muscles and a thick layer of fat under its skin.

0976velu.dexEntry: When Veluza discards unnecessary flesh, its mind becomes honed and its psychic power increases. The spare flesh has a mild but delicious flavor.

0977dond.dexEntry: This Pokémon is a glutton, but it’s bad at getting food. It teams up with a <<0978tats>> to catch prey.

0978tats.dexEntry: This is a small dragon Pokémon. It lives inside the mouth of <<0977dond>> to protect itself from enemies on the outside.

0979anni.dexEntry: When its anger rose beyond a critical point, this Pokémon gained power that is unfettered by the limits of its physical body.

0980clod.dexEntry: When attacked, this Pokémon will retaliate by sticking thick spines out from its body. It’s a risky move that puts everything on the line.

0981fari.dexEntry: Now that the brain waves from the head and tail are synced up, the psychic power of this Pokémon is 10 times stronger than <<0203gira>>’s.

0982dudu.dexEntry: This Pokémon uses its hard tail to make its nest by boring holes into bedrock deep underground. The nest can reach lengths of over six miles.

0983king.dexEntry: Only a <<0625bish>> that stands above all others in its vast army can evolve into Kingambit.

0984grea.dexEntry: Sightings of this Pokémon have occurred in recent years. The name Great Tusk was taken from a creature listed in a certain book.

0985scre.dexEntry: There has been only one reported sighting of this Pokémon. It resembles a mysterious creature depicted in an old expedition journal.

0986brut.dexEntry: It is possible that the creature listed as Brute Bonnet in a certain book could actually be this Pokémon.

0987flut.dexEntry: This Pokémon has characteristics similar to those of Flutter Mane, a creature mentioned in a certain book.

0988slit.dexEntry: This mysterious Pokémon has some similarities to a creature that an old book introduced as Slither Wing.

0989sand.dexEntry: No records exist of this Pokémon being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with a creature shown in an expedition journal.

0990iron.dexEntry: This Pokémon closely resembles a scientific weapon that a paranormal magazine claimed was sent to this planet by aliens.

0991iron.dexEntry: Its shape is similar to a robot featured in a paranormal magazine article. The robot was said to have been created by an ancient civilization.

0992iron.dexEntry: It is very similar to a cyborg covered exclusively by a paranormal magazine. The cyborg was said to be the modified form of a certain athlete.

0993iron.dexEntry: It resembles a certain Pokémon introduced in a paranormal magazine, described as the offspring of a <<0635hydr>> that fell in love with a robot.

0994iron.dexEntry: This Pokémon resembles an unknown object described in a paranormal magazine as a UFO sent to observe humanity.

0995iron.dexEntry: It has some similarities to a Pokémon introduced in a dubious magazine as a <<0248tyra>> from one billion years into the future.

0996frig.dexEntry: Frigibax absorbs heat through its dorsal fin and converts the heat into ice energy. The higher the temperature, the more energy Frigibax stores.

0997arct.dexEntry: Arctibax freezes the air around it, protecting its face with an ice mask and turning its dorsal fin into a blade of ice.

0998baxc.dexEntry: This Pokémon blasts cryogenic air out from its mouth. This air can instantly freeze even liquid-hot lava.

0999gimm.dexEntry: This Pokémon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.

1000ghol.dexEntry: Its body seems to be made up of 1,000 coins. This Pokémon gets along well with others and is quick to make friends with anybody.

1001woch.dexEntry: The grudge of a person punished for writing the king’s evil deeds upon wooden tablets has clad itself in dead leaves to become a Pokémon.

1002chie.dexEntry: This Pokémon can control 100 tons of fallen snow. It plays around innocently by leaping in and out of avalanches it has caused.

1003ting.dexEntry: The fear poured into an ancient ritual vessel has clad itself in rocks and dirt to become a Pokémon.

1004chiy.dexEntry: It controls flames burning at over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit. It casually swims through the sea of lava it creates by melting rock and sand.

1005roar.dexEntry: It is possible that this is the creature listed as Roaring Moon in an expedition journal that still holds many mysteries.

1006iron.dexEntry: It has some similarities to a mad scientist’s invention covered in a paranormal magazine.

1007kora.dexEntry: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.

1008mira.dexEntry: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles <<0967cycl>>, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.
